''Germanic cognates:'' Old Saxon [[ei]] (Dutch [[ei]]), Old High German [[ei]] (German [[Ei]]), Old Norse [[egg]] (English [[egg]], Swedish [[ägg]]).

''Indo-European cognates:'' Greek [[ωον|ᾠόν]], Latin [[ovum]] (French [[oeuf]]), Celtic ''*awio-'' (Welsh [[wy]]), Common Slavic ''[[jaje]]'' (Old Church Slavonic [[аице]], Russian [[яйцо]]), Armenian [[ձու]].

